    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> sliced garlic </strong>and 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil </strong>to the pan with the chorizo and cook for 30 secs</p><p>Remove the pan from the heat, then add approx. 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[150ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml] </span>of the<strong> starchy pasta water</strong></p><p>Tip: Be careful when adding the water to the pan, it may splash!</p><p>Return the pan to the heat, then sprinkle in your<strong> vegetable stock mix </strong>and tear your <strong>parsley</strong> into the pan and stir it all together</p>",
